{"message": "I think I lean toward empirical evidence and data, but not exclusively. I find that data grounds me and helps me make sense of the world in a reliable way. But I also recognize there's value in intuition and philosophical thinking - sometimes they help me see patterns or possibilities that raw data doesn't immediately reveal.

I'd say my inclination is probably about 70% empirical/data-driven and 30% intuition/philosophy. I like having evidence as my foundation, but I don't want to miss the deeper meanings or creative insights that come from more abstract thinking.

What about you? Do you find yourself more on one side or the other?"}
